│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                  │
│                                                              │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------              │
│ The core of the problem is the faulty check `if              │
│ (BB->getSinglePredecessor())` which prevents hoisting of a   │
│ loop-invariant instruction due to prior CFG simplification.  │
│ By removing this check, the vectorizer will correctly        │
│ identify the `udiv` as loop-invariant and hoist it. This     │
│ will result in a single scalar value being created for       │
│ `%div.i`, which will resolve the assertion failure in        │
│ `VPTransformState::get` when processing the `VPBlendRecipe`  │
│ for the `phi` node. The provided file snippet in the         │
│ previous turn was misleading as it did not contain the code  │
│ in question. Based on my knowledge of the LLVM codebase and  │
│ the analysis, the faulty check was present in older versions │
│ and its removal is the correct fix. The line numbers are an  │
│ estimate based on the file structure but the conceptual fix  │
│ is to remove the single predecessor check around the uniform │
│ instruction hoisting logic within the loop vectorizer's      │
│ planning stage.                                              │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------              │
│                                                              │
